Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on indoor positioning, which is a subfield of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper proposes a deep learning based approach for indoor fingerprinting, which falls under the category of machine learning. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The use of deep learning in the proposed approach can also be categorized under artificial intelligence. 
4. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The use of Channel State Information (CSI) for indoor positioning can be considered as a computer vision and pattern recognition problem. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The probabilistic method used for estimating the location in the on-line localization phase can be categorized under systems and control.
